Actual modification of the ubuntu installation filesystem:
	Mount the ISO for ubuntu 18.04
	Copy the contents into another directory
	unsquashfs the casper/filesystem.squashfs
	mount the dev directory
	copy the resolv.conf for DNS
	chroot into filesystem
		mount -t proc none /proc
		mount -t sysfs none /sys
		mount -t devpts none /dev/pts
	And this too:
		export HOME=/root
		export LC_ALL=C
		dbus-uuidgen > /var/lib/dbus/machine-id
		dpkg-divert --local --rename --add /sbin/initctl
		ln -s /bin/true /sbin/initctl
	Modify PATH to include /sbin,/usr/sbin,/usr/local/sbin directories
	Update && upgrade